benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Remove tags from account

covered: Valid Deletion: Successful removal scenarios (TC01-04, TC05, TC11, TC13, TC20)
Non-Existent Resource: Scenarios for non-existent account (TC06), invalid account ID format (TC07), invalid tagDef (TC08, TC18)
AUTO_PAY_OFF tag removal without default payment method: (TC10)
gaps: Soft Deletes: No tests cover soft deletion behavior
Rate Limiting: No tests cover how the system handles multiple requests in a short time
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control)
Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets
Concurrency Race Conditions: No tests cover race conditions where resources may be deleted by another user
recommendations: Add tests for soft delete behavior to ensure tags are marked as deleted but not permanently removed
Add rate limiting tests to verify the API throttles excessive requests
Add caching header tests to check for ETag and Cache-Control in responses
Add pagination tests to ensure proper handling of large tag lists
Add race condition tests where concurrent deletes on the same tag are performed to verify consistency
